    {
      "type": "TextBlock",
      "text": "When designing a card, all of the data is sent in the body of the `AdaptiveCard` JSON object. The data includes the following:",
      "wrap": true
    },
    {
      "type": "TextBlock",
      "text": "- **Elements** such as `TextBlock`, `RichTextBlock`, and `Image` are used to present content in card.\n\n- **Container Objects** such as `ActionSet`, `ColumnSet`, `Container`, `FactSet`, and `ImageSet` are used to group elements together to optimze the UI/UX Design of the card.\n\n- **Inputs** are used to display form fields in the card, so that user can consume and submit their own information. Inputs include `Text`, `Date`, `Toggle`, and `ChoiceSet`.",
      "wrap": true
    },
    {
      "type": "TextBlock",
      "text": "Webex For Developers provides a [Buttons and Cards Designer](http://developer.webex.com/buttons-and-cards-designer) that allows you to visually build a card and then copy the JSON to your application. We'll take a look into that in the next lesson.",
      "wrap": true
    },
    {
      "type": "Input.ChoiceSet",
      "id": "myCardIndex",
      "isMultiSelect": false,
      "isVisible": false,
      "choices": [
        {
          "title": "This hidden choice ensures that myCardIndex is returned with every Action.Submit attachmentAction",
